title.narrative: International Twinning Center. Quality Improvement Center

description.narrative: Reduce the transmission and impact of HIV/AIDS through support for prevention, care and treatment programs.

This award strives to reduce the transmission and impact of HIVAIDS through support for prevention, care and treatment programs. More specifically, this includes Capacity Building: The Twinning center builds sustainable institutional and human resource capacity and county ownership to address the HIV/AIDS epidemic.. Quality Improvement: Using performance measurement tools adapted to each site, the Quality Improvement Center, in conjunction with MOH, facilitates the process of data collection and reporting to improve quality in PEPFAR programs.
